subSubSection.paragraph:
Ossicles.
Dorsal body wall ossicle consists of tables in two forms. First form of table (
Figure 5A–B
) 48–62μm in diameter, spire low with 3–4 pillars; crown with 3–4 spines. Disc of first form table smooth and rounded, surface with numerous irregular perforation. Second form of table (
Figure 5I
) 88μm in diameter, spire low with four pillars; crown with four spines. Disc of second form table round; disc surface smooth with eight peripheral perforations; disc margin denticulate. Ossicles in anal region consist of tables (
Figure 5H
) measuring 74–78μm in diameter with low spire and four pillars. Disc surface smooth with eight peripheral perforations and one central perforation; disc margin denticulate. Crown of table in anal region rounded with few spines. Tube feet ossicles consist of the endplate. Endplate in tube feet (
Figure 5C
) 417μm in diameter with multiple perforations. Tentacle ossicles consist of large rods, spinose rods, small rods, and rosettes. Large rods in tentacle (
Figure 5D
) 250–367μm in length; perforated on both ends. Spinose rod in tentacle (
Figure 5F
) 242μm in length. Small rod in tentacle (
Figure 5E
) smooth with 107μm in length. Rosettes in tentacle (
Figure 5G
) 75–155μm in length.
